              <h3 class="mb-0">Recruitment</h3>
              <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-between mb-3">
                <div class="flex-grow-1">
                  <p>If you are a motivated student with a strong interest in
                    research willing to work on real world problem do not
                    hesitate to contact me for possible master's thesis,
                    internships, PhD thesis and postdocs.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-between">
                <div class="flex-grow-1">
                  <h3 class="mb-0">My research</h3>
                  <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-between mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-grow-1">
                      <p>I do computational engineering for Geosciences, working
                        on semi-automated methods to offer a more quantitative
                        qualification and characterisation of the uncertainty in
                        data and models in a merger workflow type of approach.
                        We can call it data integration, data assimilation, or
                        digital twins. My work is real world data-centric driven
                        (deep geothermal, CO2 storage), therefore, aiming to
                        support the decision making process for ressources
                        exploration and exploitation. I develop this approach
                        through different projects I lead or I contribute to,
                        with different research consortia funded by the European
                        council or the French council, which includes industry
                        and academics' partners.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
